Test Maines new ranked-choice voting system requires winning candidates to receive a majority vote. Candidates with the fewest ranked votes are eliminated, and their votes are transferred to the candidates ranked second on each voters ballot. This process continues until a candidate receives a majority. Round 2 counting is presented here as a runoff. In Round 2 counting, 3,375 votes were transferred to Adrienne Bennett, and 4,354 votes were transferred to Dale John Crafts.
